cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about weakly supervised object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an end-to-end framework and utilizes machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the stability of the result, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
